title: The Neureka context can be used and configured as expected.
narrative:
This specification covers the behavior of the Neureka class which
    exposes a global API for configuring thread local contexts and library settings.
    The purpose of this is to assert that the API exposed by the Neureka class 
    is both thread local and configurable.
    This specification also exists to cover standards for the Neureka library in general.
headers:
This specification defines what types of settings are exposed by
                    Neureka as well as more general things like how string representations
                    of various library types should look like...

blocks.text: Important settings have their expected states.

features.id: Neureka settings class can be locked causing its properties to be immutable. [0]

blocks.text: Something used to set a property and something to get the property.
Initially the property has the expected value.
We lock the settings object...
We try to set the property to another value...
The property is not changed!
We unlock the settings object...
Again we try to set the property to another value...
The property is changed!
We reset the settings object to its original state.
The properties used are boolean types.

features.id: Every Thread instance has their own Neureka instance.

blocks.text: A map containing entries for Neureka instances.
Two newly instantiated tensors store their Neureka instances in the map.
code: def t1 = new Thread({ map['instance 1'] = Neureka.get() })
def t2 = new Thread({ map['instance 2'] = Neureka.get() })

blocks.text: The tensors are being started and joined.
The map entries will no longer be filled with null.
The Neureka instances stored in the map will be different objects.
